result.execSummary:
The defendant Brittany L Stroede was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Bail Jumping-Misdemeanor, a class A misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 946.49(1)(a).

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

10:15 a.m.  Defendant present in court with Atty Barb Privat.  Lisa Vanden Branden for the State of Wisconsin.  Court recites agreement - defendant will plea to the charge.  ADA concurs.  Atty Privat concurs.  Defendant concurs.

Court goes over plea questionnaire with the defendant.  Court goes over constitutional rights with the defendant - defendant waives these rights.  Court goes over the elements of each offense.  Court instructs defendant of the maximum penalty.  Court instructs defendant regarding deportation.

Defendant enters a plea of GUILTY.  Court finds the plea is made freely, voluntarily, intelligently and understandingly.  Court finds there is a factual basis to support the plea.  Court finds the defendant guilty as charged.  Court orders the judgment of conviction be entered here today.  Statement by person.  Sentencing statement by ADA.  Sentencing statement by Atty Privat.  No statement by the defendant.

Court sentences the defendant to:  SWD, and places the defendant on probation for a period of 12 months.

CONDITIONS:

court costs
Defendant is to abide by all rules and recommendations of the supervising agent
Defendant is to complete her GED
20 hours community service

Court adjourned at 10:22 a.m.

11:30 a.m.  No appearance by the defendant.  Attorney Barb Privat present.  Andrew Christenson for the State of Wisconsin.  Statement by Atty Privat - has an offer and request defendant be brought up next week.  Court will set for plea & sentencing on May 26, 20015 at 10:00 a.m.

Court adjourned at 11:31 a.m.

1:08 p.m.  Defendant in custody and present in court without counsel.  Andrew Christenson for the State of Wisconsin.  Statement by defendant, has made contact with the PD's office.  Court will set for Status Hearing on April 20, 2015 at 1:00 p.m.  Court sets bond at $500.00 signature bond.

Court adjourned at 1:09 p.m.

2:21 p.m.  Defendant present in court without counsel.  Andrew Christenson for the State of Wisconsin.  Defendant confirms receipt of the criminal complaint and waives reading.  Court instructs the defendant of the maximum penalty on each count.  Court finds probable cause.  Court instructs the defendant of his right to an attorney.  Court determines the defendant stands mute and enters a plea of NOT GUILTY on behald of the Defendant.  Bond has been set.  Court will set for Status Hearing on April 6, 2015 at 1:00 p.m..

Defendant is to complete processing with the Green Lake County Sheriff's Department.

Court adjourned at 2:22 p.m.
